qas.question: What is the most important crop in Tibet?
What is dough made from barley flour called?
What is a popular drink in Tibet?
What seed is cultivated in Tibet?
Where is potato seed heavily cultivated?

context: The most important crop in Tibet is <a0_0>barley<a0_0/>, and dough made from barley flour—called <a1_0><b6_0>tsampa<b6_0/><a1_0/>—is the staple food of Tibet. This is either rolled into noodles or made into steamed dumplings called <a2_0><b5_0>momos<b5_0/><a2_0/>. Meat dishes are likely to be yak, goat, or mutton, often dried, or cooked into a spicy stew with potatoes. <a4_0>Mustard<a4_0/> seed is cultivated <b7_0>in Tibet<b7_0/>, and therefore features heavily in its cuisine. Yak yogurt, butter and cheese are frequently eaten, and well-prepared yogurt is considered something of a prestige item. <a3_0>Butter tea<a3_0/> is very popular to drink.
